# Hints for zsh shell

## Keybindings

### Move Cursor

* Alt + f/b: Prev/Next word
* Ctrl + a/e: Beginning/End of the command
* Ctrl + xx: Toggle btw cursor and start of line

### Edit

* Ctrl + x,e: Open command in $EDITOR, can be modifed
* Ctrl + k: Cut from cursor till end of line
* Ctrl + w: Cut from cursor till the start of line
* Ctrl + u: Cut hole line
* Ctrl + Del/d: Delete Prev/Next word from cursor
* Ctrl + y: Yank buffered text
* Ctrl + _: Undo
* Alt + r: Redo

### Processes

* Ctrl + l: Clean screen
* Ctrl + c: Signal interrupt
* Ctrl + d: Exit/logout current shell
* Ctrl + z: Move job to background

### History

* Ctrl + r: Interactiv histroy search
* Ctrl + s: Most recent command
